# Project Context — andela-security-auditor

## What we are building
An Enterprise Security Guardrail Auditor that scans Terraform and CloudFormation
infrastructure config files for security misconfigurations, calculates a Risk Score,
and visualises findings in a dashboard.

## Architect
Mayank Chugh — 20+ years enterprise delivery, HashiCorp Terraform certified.
He directs. You execute. No manual code edits by Mayank.

## Core constraints
- Python 3.11+ only
- FastAPI for API layer
- SQLite for database (no external DB)
- Streamlit for dashboard
- No cloud resources — runs entirely local or free tier
- All code must be complete — no TODOs, no placeholders
- Type hints on all functions
- Update prompts.md after every change

## Security rules to implement
- PUBLIC_S3_BUCKET — Critical — 40pts
- OPEN_SSH — High — 25pts
- OPEN_RDP — High — 25pts
- OPEN_ALL_PORTS — Critical — 40pts
- NO_MFA — Medium — 20pts
- WEAK_IAM_POLICY — Medium — 20pts
- UNENCRYPTED_EBS — High — 25pts
- HTTP_LISTENER — Medium — 20pts

## Risk score
min(sum of all finding points, 100)
0=clean, 1-25=Low, 26-50=Medium, 51-75=High, 76-100=Critical

## API endpoints
POST /scan — file upload, returns findings + score
GET /scans — scan history
GET /scans/{scan_id} — scan detail
GET /health — health check

